<title>Strange Maps, Julius Scissor and cycle thefts</title>
<description>&lt;p&gt;Have you discovered the &lt;a href="http://strangemaps.wordpress.com"&gt;Strange Maps&lt;/a&gt; blog? It&amp;#8217;s consistently excellent but &lt;a href="http://strangemaps.wordpress.com/2009/02/01/358-huns-hair-salons-and-puns/"&gt;this recent entry&lt;/a&gt;, which snips a very strange map from &lt;a href="http://www.zeit.de/"&gt;Die Zeit&lt;/a&gt;, is a cut above the rest.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://strangemaps.wordpress.com/2009/02/01/358-huns-hair-salons-and-puns/"&gt;&lt;img src="http://strangemaps.files.wordpress.com/2009/02/friseur.jpg?w=600&amp;h=731" width="600" height="731" alt="German hairdressers"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;span id="continue-reading"/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reading through the comments, I learn &lt;a href="http://www.ziet.de"&gt;Die Ziet&lt;/a&gt; has been running a series featuring &lt;a href="http://www.zeit.de/themen/leben/gesellschaft/deutschlandkarten/index-deutschlandkarten"&gt;similarly imaginative cartographics&lt;/a&gt;. Here are the German &lt;a href="http://www.zeit.de/2008/40/Karte-40"&gt;cycle theft hotspots&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.zeit.de/2008/40/Karte-40"&gt;&lt;img src="http://zeus.zeit.de/bilder/2008/40/leben/zeit-magazin-leben/diebstahl-karte/diebstahl-karte-800.gif" width="600" height="822" alt="Cycle theft in Germany"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description>
<dc:date>2009-02-02</dc:date>
<guid>http://tag.wordaligned.org/posts/strange-maps-julius-scissor-and-cycle-thefts</guid>
